    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm doing the drywall in a small bathroom and im about to start the taping and mudding phase. can u walk me through the best way to do the seams so i dont end up with visible cracks or bumps later? thanks.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When taping and mudding drywall seams, a good practice is to use a technique called \"three-coat application.\" Start with a thin layer of mud over the tape to embed it, letting it dry completely between coats. For subsequent coats, feather the edges of the mud out wide to blend the seam seamlessly with the existing wall surface. This gradual feathering prevents sharp transitions that lead to visible cracking or bumps.",
      "source": "target",
