      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Small cracks near the baseboard area are often due to substrate movement or general settling, not necessarily poor taping. To patch these small holes, first clean out any loose debris and lightly dampen the area before applying a small amount of lightweight joint compound. Use a flexible corner bead or a mesh patch over the area to reinforce the joint before applying mud, which helps prevent the crack from reappearing.",
